#: ../../F/fall-through.rst:13
msgid ""
"To exit a loop by exhaustion, i.e., by having fulfilled its exit condition "
"rather than via a break or exception condition that exits from the middle of"
" it. This usage appears to be *really* old, dating from the 1940s and 1950s."
msgstr ""
"ループを、途中から抜け出すbreakや例外条件によってではなく、終了条件を満たすことによって、すなわち出尽くしによって抜けること。この用法は\\ "
"*かなり*\\ 古いようで、1940年代から1950年代にさかのぼる。"

#: ../../F/fall-through.rst:17
msgid ""
"To fail a test that would have passed control to a subroutine or some other "
"distant portion of code."
msgstr "制御をサブルーチンやコードの離れた部分に渡すはずだったテストに失敗すること。"

#: ../../F/fall-through.rst:20
msgid ""
"In C, ‘fall-through’ occurs when the flow of execution in a switch statement"
" reaches a :code:`case` label other than by jumping there from the switch "
"header, passing a point where one would normally expect to find a "
":code:`break`\\. A trivial example:"
msgstr ""
"Cでは、switch文中の実行の流れが、switchのヘッダーからそこへジャンプするのではなく、\\ :code:`break`\\ "
"があると普通は予想される地点を通り過ぎて、\\ :code:`case`\\ ラベルに到達したときに‘fall-through’が起こる。ささいな例："

#: ../../F/fall-through.rst:42
msgid "The variant spelling /\\* FALL THRU \\*/ is also common."
msgstr "変種の表記/\\* FALL THRU \\*/もよく見られる。"

#: ../../F/fall-through.rst:44
msgid ""
"The effect of the above code is to :manpage:`do_green()` when color is "
":code:`GREEN`\\, :manpage:`do_red()` when color is :code:`RED`\\, "
":manpage:`do_blue()` on any other color other than :code:`PINK`\\, and (and "
"this is the important part) :manpage:`do_pink()` *and then* "
":manpage:`do_red()` when color is :code:`PINK`\\. Fall-through is "
":ref:`considered-harmful` by some, though there are contexts (such as the "
"coding of state machines) in which it is natural; it is generally considered"
" good practice to include a comment highlighting the fall-through where one "
"would normally expect a break. See also :ref:`Duffs-device`\\."
msgstr ""
"上記のコードの効果は、colorが\\ :code:`GREEN`\\ のとき\\ :manpage:`do_green()`\\ を、\\ "
":code:`RED`\\ のとき\\ :manpage:`do_red()`\\ を、\\ :code:`PINK`\\ 以外の他のどの色でも\\ "
":manpage:`do_blue()`\\ を、そして(ここが重要な部分だが)colorが\\ :code:`PINK`\\ のとき\\ "
":manpage:`do_pink()`\\ \\ *の後に*\\ \\ :manpage:`do_red()`\\ を実行することである。Fall-"
"throughは一部の人には\\ :ref:`considered-harmful`\\ "
"とされるが、(状態機械のコーディングなど)それが自然な文脈もある。普通ならbreakを予想する箇所のfall-"
"throughを強調するコメントを入れるのが、一般に良い習慣とされる。\\ :ref:`Duffs-device`\\ も参照。"
